Uses of Package
owlSpeak.engine

  • Packages that use owlSpeak.engine 
    Package Description
    owlSpeak
    This package contains all classes needed to access and modify the Spoken Dialogue Ontologies and provides a ready-to-use factory class.
    owlSpeak.engine
    This package provides all classes the controller needs to generate the next dialogue steps.
    owlSpeak.engine.his
    This package provides all classes for extending the dialogue control to the hidden information state approach.
    owlSpeak.engine.his.sysAction  
    owlSpeak.engine.his.util  
    owlSpeak.engine.policy  
    owlSpeak.engine.systemState  
    owlSpeak.lgus  
    owlSpeak.plugin
    This package provides all classes of the plugin modules.
    owlSpeak.quality  
    owlSpeak.servlet
    This package provides the classes that define the various views OwlSpeak supports.
    owlSpeak.servlet.grammar  
    owlSpeak.util
    This package provides utilities that are not core features of the controller.
  • Classes in owlSpeak.engine used by owlSpeak 
    Class and Description
    OwlSpeakOntology
    encapsulates all OwlSpeakOntology access
  • Classes in owlSpeak.engine used by owlSpeak.engine 
    Class and Description
    Core
    contains the ontologies-Vector, the OwlSpeakOntology actualOnto and the RespawnManager respawnManager
    CoreMove
    owlSpeak Class CoreMove is the basic Move/Agenda/OwlSpeakOntology triplet used for the engine
    OwlSpeakOntology
    encapsulates all OwlSpeakOntology access
    ProbModel
    The class that maintains all the probabilities required for updating the belief states of a Slot.
    RespawnManager
    owlSpeak Class RespawnManager allows access to multiple Respawn and encapsulates reading / writing
    Settings
    owlSpeak Class Settings is used for reading / writing the settings of the Controller
    Settings.Ontology
    Class Ontology stores a name, a description and a file for reading and writing ontologies to disk
    Settings.UserOntoSetting
    Class UserOntoSetting stores an ontoname and ontostatus for individual users
    Settings.Usersetting
    Class Usersetting stores settings for the individual user
    Slot
    The class that represents a POMDP Slot.
